<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="likely-adv">likely <strong><em>adv</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /'laɪkli/    美 /'laɪkli/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-most-more-very">1.★ <strong>[常与most, more, very连用] 可能</strong></h4>
<p>probably：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>When one wolf starts to howl, <strong>very likely</strong> others will follow.  
当一只狼嚎叫起来，其他的狼很可能也跟着叫。</p><footer>2011 湖北</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="not-likely">Not likely!</h3>
<p>1.<strong>[表示强烈的否定] 绝不可能！才不呢！</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Would she mind playing against her former teammates? 
她介意和她以前的队友比赛吗？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Not likely!  
不会！</p><footer>2010 浙江改</footer></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Studies show that people are more <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (可能) to suffer from back problems if they always sit before computer screens for long hours.  （2011 陕西改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. likely  </p></div>